title: Short Poetry Collection 119
description:
LibriVox's Short Poetry Collection 119. This is a collection of 28 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for April 2013.

This project contains the following:
Abide With Me by Henry F. Lyte (1793-1847)
Annabel Lee by Edgar Allan Poe (1809-1849)
Approach of Night by Charles G. Blanden (1857-1938)
Ashes of Life by Edna St. Vincent Millay (1892-1950)
The Ballad of Blasphemous Bill by Robert W. Service (1874-1958)
Chiquita, La Bonita by William Lightfoot Visscher (1842-1924)
The Everlasting Snows by Helen Hay (1875-1944)
The Fairies by William Allingham (1824-1889)
Fairy Song by Louisa May Alcott (1832-1888)
The Farmer by Freeman Edwin Miller (1864-1951)
The Harlot's House by Oscar Wilde (1854-1900)
Hope is the Thing With Feathers by Emily Dickinson (1830-1886)
I Hear America Singing by Walt Whitman (1812-1892)
The Inner Silence by Harriet Monroe (1860-1936)
I Wandered Lonely as a Cloud by William Wordsworth (1770-1850)
The Little Ghost by Edna St. Vincent Millay (1892-1950)
The Lonely House by Emily Dickinson (1830-1886)
Mother O' Mine by Rudyard Kipling (1865-1936)
Of All the Sounds despatched abroad by Emily Dickinson (1830-1886)
Old Accustomed Impudent Ghost by Emanuel Carnevali (1897-1942)
Pear Tree by Hilda Doolittle (1886-1961)
The Raven by Edgar Allen Poe (1809-1849)
The Runes on Weland's Sword by Rudyard Kipling (1865-1936)
Snowflakes by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow (1807-1882)
Sonnet 43 (How Do I Love Thee) by Elizabeth Barrett Browning (1806-1861)
A Superscription by Dante Gabriel Rossetti (1828-1882)
Times Go by Turns by Robert Southwell (1561-1595)
Year of Meteors by Walt Whitman (1819-1892)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
